Very tasty pastries and delicious, carefully made drinks. They serve stumptown coffee and sell a good variety of it as well. Prices are good and the staff are very friendly and helpful. They are open reduced hours during the pandemic, support them!

Great spot for strong Stumptown coffee roasted daily, with all the bakery goods you’d probably want and a few tasty food items on the menu too. Friendly staff. Small interior space but enough to read the news or have a chat, along with outside benches to sip a latte on a nice day. A great pick-up point for hot or cold brew before heading up to Grand Army Plaza or Prospect Park, or some window shopping on Flatbush or even better Vanderbilt, which is right up Sterling. One day maybe they’ll conclude the near continuous and eternal street work on Sterling nearby (which is haphazard and not all that noisy).

Very Nice cafe. Only reason for 4stars is that, there is no restroom and  it is in a very busy and important crossroads location between the Brooklyn Public Library and Barclays Center. Great place to stop and refresh, people watch, write... but alas no restroom . Otherwise...it is a great cafe, great staff, and there is a vegan muffin option!  If you want to grab and go ... this is a great cafe. There are a few seats with tables, a window bar/stool and a couple of benches out front. Great views of Flatbush Avenue.
If you prefer Night Courtados to cortados- don't say I kept it a secret.

We got hot chocolates from here after a particularly wet, cold, and windy day. It hit the spot-I recommend getting the hot chocolate with the oat milk if you can’t have dairy. Pretty art and really, really delicious!! Small space with limited standing and sitting room, so hit up another hungry ghost if you’re set on this chain but need more space.

Best coffee around!!! Some delish baked goods and sandwiches too. Great music, and staff is classic hipster fun :)  this location is smaller than their other cafes, so it's usually better as a to-go option -- or for sitting solo / with one friend only, good for people-watching, or with a book -- especially during busy times (if you want to set up shop with your laptop or bring 2+ people, you may prefer to walk a few blocks down to their larger flatbush location, near doughnut plant).

Neighborhood coffee spot. Small, quiet and nestled in lovely, Prospect Heights, Brooklyn. The wait person that actually serves up the food is rather pleasant and nice to connect with.  However, the fellow who usually rings you up comes off sort of grumpy and tired. I hope that changes for the better.  Perhaps they should switch roles  sometimes and switch to make a healthy chnage, or perspective?
Macchiato was good, but my bagel was far from it. Maybe bc it was New Years Day, and the bakery was closed?  Darn thing was rock hard, and it shouldn't have been sold. I won't be back.

Great satellite location to their main location on Flatbush. Not as large of a food variety but great esspresso and tea. Cozy. All stools.

Good atmosphere and reasonably priced coffee and teas. Two locations downtown, so in case one is crowded, you can try the other one. Friendly staff.

Good coffee shop for stopping by and grabbing a morning (or afternoon) latte and pastry. Hungry Ghost serves Stumptown coffee, which is a mark of quality for any coffee shop, and everything I've ordered has been good!  There is a couple of Hungry Ghost store fronts in this area, and this location is by far the smallest. It is more of a grab-and-go spot while you're on your way to Prospect Park than a coffee date spot.

Great little coffee shop with very limited seating at this location. The one down Vanderbilt and Bergen has more seating. Gets a little crowded at peak times since it's a local favorite, but the line always seems longer than it actually is because of the small size. Bagels and baked goods are delivered fresh every morning, but go quickly. You're really here for the coffee anyway.. which is Stumptown (yum!). Cold brew is strong and on a proper tap. Baristas are very down to earth and make a great drink.
Great coffee neighborhood spot
Clean and customer friendly spot for relaxing

Coffee is a weakness of mine, especially an ice coffee on a hot day. Thankfully my husband and I came in when it wasn't crowded, and we grabbed a seat. Some music played that reminded me of high school,  and not in a bad way. The employees were pretty friendly, and the coffee was quite tasty and refreshing. Prices are pretty reasonable too, for those of us that can handle our coffee straight up. Perked me right up after the previous two places I went to had rude employees.
My favorite daily cappuccino! Great place, awesome baristas and good prices!
the multi grain croissant. you won't regret it.
Quaint coffee shop. Excellent area, great iced coffee, good iced tea. They were out of sandwiches at 1230p (on a Monday), but there were other tasty snacks to choose from.

With its tiny storefront, this Hungry Ghost is definitely more of a grab-and-go location, as differentiated from the larger more inviting outpost a few blocks up Flatbush. It does the job when you're in the area.

This is the douchiest coffee shop in all of Brooklyn. The "please don't use laptops at these tables" signs are a good indicator of that, followed by the tall staff member who acts like he's doing you a favor by serving you coffee. To top it off, if you do try to connect your laptop to the wifi in one of the 6 "allowed" spots, it won't work and the staff won't be willing to do you the simple favor of restarting it. Hope these guys go out of business and make room for some kind humans and good service!

A neighborhood staple with awesome service, great coffees, a huge selection of teas and basic snacks for when you're feeling hungry. Lots of comfortable seating including a few benches outdoors make this a popular place to catch up with neighbors.  There's a reason they have so many regulars!
They have delicious bagels from Bagel Hole on 7th ave. Coffee is also quite good and you can choose your roast (medium or dark).

Good coffee, great soup. small space, but fast and friendly service. Solid wifi, but unfortunately no place to plug in...More suited to a quick lunch than a longer lingering afternoon. Great selection of pastries and pann's and a lunch combo or two. They don't have a restroom open to the public.
Good solid coffee option in Prospect Heights, with the optional side of pastries from Balthazar. Small cafe feel with nice menu options, including sandwiches during lunch hours.
